---

## How everything connects

```
User selects Source + Target language
        ↓
Tap scan button
        ↓
PixelCopy grabs current AR camera frame as Bitmap
        ↓
ML Kit Text Recognition → finds text blocks + screen bounding boxes
        ↓
TranslationProcessor → translates each block individually
        ↓
arRenderer.placeAnchors() → ARCore hit-tests each block's
screen center → finds real-world plane → creates Anchor
        ↓
GL thread every frame:
  • backgroundRenderer draws live camera feed
  • Each AnchoredTextBlock rendered as a billboard quad
  • Billboard always faces camera (makeBillboard)
  • Translated text texture baked as Bitmap → GL texture
  • Text sticks to real surface as you walk around
        ↓
Tap Clear → anchors detached, ready to scan again
```

---

## Key architecture decisions

| Decision | Why |
|---|---|
| `PixelCopy` for screen capture | Only way to grab pixels from a `GLSurfaceView` correctly |
| `glSurfaceView.queueEvent()` for anchor placement | ARCore anchors must be created on the GL thread |
| Billboard shader | Translated text always faces camera — readable from any angle |
| Bitmap → GL texture per block | Lets you render rich styled text (font, color, corners) in OpenGL without a UI framework |
| Plane detection enabled | Lets ARCore find real surfaces to anchor text onto precisely |
| Fallback anchor 0.5m ahead | Handles cases where no plane is detected yet |